description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic, well motivated individual with great attention to detail and an interest in patient pathway analysis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require an RTT Validator to support the validation team to ensure patients are seen within a timely manner. This will involve analysing patient pathways and exploring the next steps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be competent in Microsoft office/ Excel. Previous experience with Referral to Treatment times (RTT) and use of hospital systems would be desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of the benefits of working at YDH include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working for a Trust voted 1st for Health and Well-being across the UK (NHS staff survey)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full NHS terms and conditions including extensive holidays, Agenda for Change pay with enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounts for local and national retailers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated well-being services for all employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working where possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time position 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jessica Whatley Operational Service Manager jessica.whatley@ydh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;David Waring Patient Pathway Manager david.waring@ydh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
